ons in Setting Treatment Standards </ITAG><ITAG tagnum="24">  a. Use of Extraction Procedure (EP) Toxicity Data </ITAG><ITAG tagnum="24">  b. Treatment Standards Based on Single Facility Data </ITAG><ITAG tagnum="24">  c. Demonstrated and Available Technologies </ITAG><ITAG tagnum="24">  d. Selection of BDAT Constituents </ITAG><ITAG tagnum="24"> 8. Treatment Investigations for All Second Third Wastes and Presentationof All Proposed Treatment Standards </ITAG><ITAG tagnum="24">  a. Cyanide Wastes </ITAG><ITAG tagnum="24">   (1) Wastes from the Metal Finishing Industry [F006, F007, F008,F009, F010, F011, F012, F019] </ITAG><ITAG tagnum="24">   (2) Wastes from Acrylonitrile Production [K011, K013, K014] </ITAG><ITAG tagnum="24">   (3) Cyanide Wastes Designated as Either U or P Wastes [P013, P021,P029, P030, P063, P074, P098, P099, P104, P106, P121] </ITAG><ITAG tagnum="24">   (4) Cyanide Wastes Designated as D003 Reactive </ITAG><ITAG tagnum="24">  b. Wastes from Chlorinated Aliphatics Production [F024] </ITAG><ITAG tagnum="24">  c. Wastes from Pigment Production [K002, K003, K004, K005, K006,K007, K008] </ITAG><ITAG tagnum="24">  d. Wastes from Acetaldehyde Production [K009, K010] </ITAG><ITAG tagnum="24">  e. Wastes from the Production of Ethylene Dichloride and Nitrobenzene[K019, K025] </ITAG><ITAG tagnum="24">  f. Wastes from Phthalic Anhydride Production [K023, K093, K094]</ITAG><ITAG tagnum="24">  g. Wastes from the Production of Dinitrotoluene, Toluene Diamene,and Toluene Diisocyanate [K027, K111, K112, K113, K114, K115, K116, U221,U223] </ITAG><ITAG tagnum="24">  h. Wastes from 1,1,1-Trichloroethane Production [K028, K029, K095,K096] </ITAG><ITAG tagnum="24">  i. Wastes from Phorate Production [K038, K039, K040] </ITAG><ITAG tagnum="24">  j. Wastes from 2,4-D Production [K043] </ITAG><ITAG tagnum="24">  k. Second Third K Wastes For Which No Standards are Proposed [K041,K042, K097, K098, K105] </ITAG><ITAG tagnum="24">  l. Other Organophosphorus Wastes [K036, P